De_Beacon_b1 Made by h4mx0r (h4mx0r@gmail.com) Counter-Terrorists: You have set off a signal beacon to alert your countries as to the location of a certain terrorist group in an obscure part of northern Russia. Defend this beacon until signal is recieved and reinforcements are en route. Terrorists: A leak in intellegence has alerted your organization to several Covert Ops in the area. Undoubtedly they will be attempting to alert their superiors as to the location of your organization. Stop them at all costs or disrupt the signal by planting a bomb in certain spots on any of the buildings.
Notes: This is beta1. I do not intend to continue to finish this map due to lack of interest. However it is playable at this point, although still a little ugly. If people like this map, and truly desire further work on it, I may reconsider pushing further with this map.
This is a small little map. Almost small enough to be and FY. T's start near the water and the CT's start up top. The T make their way up to plant the bomb. Can you?

The map supports maximum teams of 24v24. There are 3 bombspots, 2 outside the bunker and 1 inside. T's start at the beach, CT's in the bunker.
Map includes custom soundscapes and sounds, full bot nav and map overview.

Theory Behind Map:

Ever since 1.3 (I stopped playing after 1.3 until Source), I always wanted to do a map of this sort - with a realistic battle feel of rushing up a beach to take a strongpoint. With the old HL engine, it simply wasnt possible due to its limitations.
Soon as HL2 came out, I realised it was possible. With the excellent remake of de_prodigy, a lot of the textures that I would be needing were there ready.
So, I put it into Hammer and have made it :)

This is also timed with the 3 year existence of my clan, SFS.


The map was also originally planned to include HDR after it had been released for CS:Source, however, the map file increased from 8Mb to a whooping 31Mb. Nobody is going to download a map that big, so I decided to take it for that reason alone. Which is a big shame, as it really made the map a LOT better.

Bottom line is, enjoy the map. Some good battles can be had and is great for that long range practising.

This is by no means my first map.  However, it is the first map I would like to release to the public.  I know the map isn't that impressive, though I do hope someone will be able to enjoy this map.  I plan on releasing more grand maps later on, apon there completion.


Map Name:  De_BattleGrounds

Files Includes:  De_BattleGrounds.BSP, and De_BattleGrounds.NAV

Map Creator:  [AKA] ENIGMA (Me)

Map Description:  The basic mechanics of this map are stradegy.  I added barriers and walls which provide sufficent cover for the small map.  As usual the object for the Terrorists is to deliver the bomb, while the Counter-Terrorists try to prevent it.

Special Features:  There is, I promise, a hidden(invisible)teleporter.  The teleporter will take you one place, were there after you will have to find a second teleporter which will prevent your death and take you to the bomb-site.  Sorry for the not so detailed explaination, that is because it is up to you to figure out.

*Special Note*:  It would appreciated that no one copy/alter this map without my permission.  I may grant permission for alteration of this map, if you would like to reach me to dicuss this you can contact me at FpsBanana or with my email: Nickdon1017@gmail.com

Above all, enjoy the map.

**Installation**
1.  Take the cstrike folder and drag it into you Counter-Strike Source folder.  If it asks for you to overwrite folders, just say "yes" or "yes to all".

(DIRECTORY(Such as, C):\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\USERNAME\counter-strike source) <--Example.  Your counter-strike source folder may be found else-where.

de_bastion2 is a port with remake of the de_bastion2 from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.
Description:

Bastion2 - Bomb/Defuse

Outraged by the corrupt bourgeoisie bidding decadent sums on useless pieces of paint and canvas, Anarchists planned to bomb a historic castle in the south of France and its current art exhibition. News of the attack leaked to the gendarmerie, who called off the auction and evacuated the prominent bidders. A GIGN special operations unit has been dispatched to the scene to neutralise the threat.

Counter-Terrorists:

Garrison the historic bastion and repel the Anarchist's assault!

Terrorists:

Plant and detonate the C4 at one of the art exhibition sites!
